text:

text: Interesting: When Wuhan was locked down on Jan. 23, some countries showed utter unconcern and even schadenfreude. A month later, the virus struck Italy, then Europe fell silent. Two weeks on, the outbreak hit the U.S., it didn't keep silent, but rather started buck-passing.

text: Welcome to my Twitter account. In my first tweet, I'd like to address an important development. Recently, the CPC issued a joint appeal with over 230 political parties in more than 100 countries, urging all countries to enhance cooperation against the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/KVMl71SJuQ
